      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SWEET MILLIE (5) flew the lids from out wide with a slick early split but ran over at the finish when a narrow fourth (24.41) over 425m at this track. Has winning claims on her best figures. ELEVENTH SCOTCH (6) drew an outside box and got into the minors when a 2 length third (22.68) at Warrnambool in Bottom Up - Grade 5. Missed the placings only try here. Some good form is emerging from his last run. Leading chance. CHIEF HAMISH (1) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing fourth (23.03) in a Grade 5 at Geelong. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings four times from eight starts. Key player if finds best. CORNHILL RAVEN (2) took charge early and was never headed last time out. Sure to figure prominently.",
